  "prompt": "My girlfriend for 4years cheated 3 times. I found out 2 month ago. She started talking to a guy as a friend. He called her babe, what should I do?",
  "response": "Based on the history of multiple past infidelities and this new suspicious communication, here are some recommendations:\n\n1. Communicate directly:\n- Ask her clearly about her relationship with this guy\n- Express your concerns about her past cheating\n- See how she responds and if she's transparent\n\n2. Set clear boundaries:\n- Make it known that calling her \"babe\" is inappropriate\n- Ask her to stop communicating with him if the interactions seem inappropriate\n- Be firm about your expectations\n\n3. Consider your options:\n- Do you still trust her after multiple past betrayals?\n- Can you genuinely forgive and rebuild trust?\n- Is this relationship still healthy for you?\n\n4. Protect yourself emotionally:\n- Don't accept repeated disrespect\n- Be prepared to walk away if she's not committed\n- Prioritize your mental and emotional well-being\n\n5. Potentially seek counseling:\n- Individual counseling for yourself\n- Couples counseling if you both want to repair the relationship\n\nKey points:\n- Multiple past cheating incidents are a serious red flag\n- Her current behavior seems suspicious\n- Your trust has been significantly damaged\n\nUltimately, you must decide if this relationship is worth continuing or if it's time to move on and find someone who respects you fully.",
